caption.p: Prevalence of age-specific hrHPV infection and corresponding 95% confidence intervals in study population. (A) Overall age-specific hrHPV prevalence: significant difference in ≤19 years and ≥50 years compared with any other age group ( Ps < 0.001), (B) Comparison of age-specific hrHPV infection between two regions (Wuhan district vs. Zhejiang district): significant difference in age-groups of 20-39, 40-49 and ≥50 ( Ps < 0.001) .
